  "text": "Trace how Firefox's Servo-based CSS style system resolves and applies styles to DOM elements. Find all C++ source files in `mozilla-firefox/firefox` under `layout/style/` that form the core style resolution pipeline: 1. The header and source files for `ServoStyleSet` \u2014 the main entry point for style resolution. 2. The header for `ServoBindings` \u2014 the Gecko-to-Servo FFI declarations. 3. The header for `RestyleManager` \u2014 the component that schedules and manages style recalculation. 4. The header for `ServoUtils` \u2014 utility functions for Servo traversal state. 5. The `moz.build` file for `layout/style/` that lists all the style system source files. Report the repo, file path, and key class or FFI function name for each file.",
